'''[[新加坡|新加坡]]'''的[[LGBT|LGBT]]人士会面对非LGBT人士所不会面对的法律问题。[[男同性恋|男同性恋]][[同性性行为|同性性行为]]在新加坡並不合法，但已鮮少執行有關法律。在[[跨性别|跨性别]]人士方面，新加坡于1971年首次进行[[变性手术|变性手术]]，并于两年后允许已接受手术者更易合法性别<ref>[http://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/recognised-legally-but-challenges-remain Recognised legally, but challenges remain] {{Wayback|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/recognised-legally-but-challenges-remain|date=20161006042605}}, The Straits Times, 19 September 2016.</ref>。

== 历史背景 ==
=== 《刑法》第377A条 ===
新加坡曾为英国殖民地，其《[[新加坡刑法|刑法]]》源自同样被英国统治的印度。原本的第377条将任何与其他人或动物进行的“非自然”性交媾行为视为违法；另一条文为第377A条，其将男性之间的“严重猥亵”（gross indecency）视为有罪。<ref>{{cite web|title=Penal Code - Singapore Statutes Online|url=https://sso.agc.gov.sg/Act/PC1871|access-date=30 September 2018|website=sso.agc.gov.sg|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180930233230/https://sso.agc.gov.sg/Act/PC1871|archive-date=30 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>2007年，[[新加坡国会|新加坡国会]]对《刑法》进行重大修订与辩论，其决定废除原有的第377条，并将[[奸尸|奸尸]]罪取而代之，第377A条则予以保留。2013年，一对[[男同性恋|男同性恋]]伴侣林明釧（Gary Lim）和朱文良（Kenneth Chee）以及另一名男同性恋者分别提出法律挑战，指第377A条违反《[[新加坡宪法|宪法]]》第9条和第12条，其案件被驳回之后，[[新加坡上诉庭|上诉庭]]于隔年再次驳回他们的上诉。<ref>[http://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/courts-crime/court-of-appeal-rules-that-section-377a-that-criminalises-sex-between-men-is Court of Appeal rules that Section 377A that criminalises sex between men is constitutional] {{Wayback|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/courts-crime/court-of-appeal-rules-that-section-377a-that-criminalises-sex-between-men-is |date=20161005150730 }}, The Straits Times, 29 October 2014.</ref><ref>〈[http://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/trad/world/2014/10/141030_singapore_gay_court 人權組織譴責新加坡法院同性戀裁決] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/trad/world/2014/10/141030_singapore_gay_court |date=20161005205109 }}〉，BBC，2014年10月30日。</ref>在新加坡，第377A条仍然偶尔被执行。2007年至2013年期间，共有9人依377A条款被定罪。<ref name="economist">{{Cite news|url=https://www.economist.com/blogs/banyan/2014/10/gay-rights-singapore|title=Gay rights in Singapore: On permanent parole|newspaper=The Economist|location=London|date=30 October 2014|access-date=13 July 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170716074722/https://www.economist.com/blogs/banyan/2014/10/gay-rights-singapore|archive-date=16 July 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>

== 同性婚姻 ==
在婚姻方面，《[[妇女宪章|妇女宪章]]》第12条第1款规定，在结婚当天，完婚双方必须是男性与女性，意指[[同性婚姻|同性婚姻]]无效。不过，同一条例的第2款列明，一名已通过变性手术者与异性者的婚姻永远有效，第3款也说明双方的性别以身份证上所注明为准，这代表已接受手术的变性者有权与异性通婚。<ref>{{Cite web|title=《妇女宪章》第9条|url=http://statutes.agc.gov.sg/aol/search/display/view.w3p;ident=e84195b9-a923-4c69-86de-36b316699b17;page=0;query=DocId%3A%22f0897dd7-1f3a-45a9-b1e7-ba30fef2dbba%22%20Status%3Ainforce%20Depth%3A0;rec=0#pr9-he-.|accessdate=2016-10-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161005200820/http://statutes.agc.gov.sg/aol/search/display/view.w3p;ident=e84195b9-a923-4c69-86de-36b316699b17;page=0;query=DocId%3A%22f0897dd7-1f3a-45a9-b1e7-ba30fef2dbba%22%20Status%3Ainforce%20Depth%3A0;rec=0#pr9-he-.|archive-date=2016-10-05|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 收养/抚养权 ==
在新加坡，同性恋者收养儿童是非法的。

2018年12月，一个罕见的事件曾被破例允许，一名新加坡同性恋者通过代孕获得了他在美国生下的孩子的收养权。新加坡高等法院推翻了2017年一名法官裁定该男子不能合法收养他的儿子的裁决，这是因为他是通过[[體外受精|体外受精]]（仅限于异性恋已婚夫妇）受孕并通过代孕获得儿子的。<ref>{{cite web|title=Gay Singaporean man can adopt son born via surrogacy, court rules|url=https://amp.cnn.com/cnn/2018/12/17/asia/singapore-gay-rights-intl/index.html|access-date=2018-12-18|date=2018-02-17|work=CNN|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181217184630/https://amp.cnn.com/cnn/2018/12/17/asia/singapore-gay-rights-intl/index.html|archive-date=2018-12-17|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Gay Singaporean man wins landmark appeal to adopt surrogate child|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-46588830|access-date=2018-12-18|date=2018-12-17|last=Tan|first=Yvette|work=BBC News|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181217180229/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-46588830|archive-date=2018-12-17|url-status=live}}</ref>

== 国民服役 ==
2003年之前，新加坡禁止[[同性恋|同性恋者]]在民防部队中担任一些“敏感职位”。<ref>{{cite news|date=2003-07-07|work=[[Time_(magazine)|Time Asia]]|location=香港|title=The Lion In Winter|url=http://www.time.com/time/asia/covers/501030707/sea_singapore4.html|first=Simon|last=Elegant|access-date=2007-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070203141611/http://www.time.com/time/asia/covers/501030707/sea_singapore4.html|archive-date=2007-02-03|url-status=dead}}</ref>过去，一些国民服役人员曾被鼓励参加[[LGBT迴轉治療|迴轉治療]]。部分承认自己为同性恋者的新加坡国民服役人员被排除在军官培训之外，有些则被拒绝获得在军队中担任某些特殊角色所需的安全许可。<ref>{{cite news|title=What's It Like To Come Out As Gay To The SAF?|url=https://www.ricemedia.co/culture-people-homosexuality-saf/|access-date=2020-09-05|work=RICE|date=2020-06-27|archive-date=2021-12-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211210230850/https://www.ricemedia.co/culture-people-homosexuality-saf/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 回转治疗 ==
2006年1月，[[新加坡社区发展、青年及体育部|社区发展、青年及体育部]] (MCYS) 向隶属于[[脫離同性戀|“脱离同性恋”运动]]的组织 Liberty League 拨款10万新元，以促进[[LGBT迴轉治療|回转治疗]]。该组织表示它“促进个人、家庭和社会的性别和性健康”。<ref>{{cite web|title=Singapore government awards S$100,000 grant to group with ex-gay affiliation|url=http://www.fridae.asia/gay-news/2006/01/17/1559.singapore-government-awards-s-100000-grant-to-group-with-ex-gay-affiliation|access-date=2016-07-04|author=Sylvia Tan|date=2006-01-17|publisher=Fridae.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160817145503/http://www.fridae.asia/gay-news/2006/01/17/1559.singapore-government-awards-s-100000-grant-to-group-with-ex-gay-affiliation|archive-date=2016-08-17|url-status=live}}</ref>然而，迫于同性恋维权人士的压力，Liberty League 将这笔赠款退还给了该部，该组织自2014年起已不复存在。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Conversion Therapy Bans - Enshrining a Contested View of Human Nature in Law|author=|url=https://journalsonline.academypublishing.org.sg/Journals/Singapore-Academy-of-Law-Journal/Current-Issue/ctl/eFirstSALPDFJournalView/mid/494/ArticleId/1616/Citation/JournalsOnlinePDF|last=Lee|first=Darius|date=2021-03-11|journal=Singapore Academy of Law Journal|volume=33|pages=483-530|access-date=2022-03-06|archive-date=2021-06-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210624212104/https://journalsonline.academypublishing.org.sg/Journals/Singapore-Academy-of-Law-Journal/Current-Issue/ctl/eFirstSALPDFJournalView/mid/494/ArticleId/1616/Citation/JournalsOnlinePDF}}</ref>

2020年5月，时任[[新加坡卫生部|卫生部长]][[颜金勇|颜金勇]]在对官委议员王丽婷（{{Lang-en|Anthea Ong}}）的提问的书面答复中表明了政府反对回转治疗的立场。回复内容如下：“（卫生部）希望医生和其他医疗保健专业人员根据循证最佳实践和临床伦理进行实践，并在提供护理时考虑和尊重患者的偏好和情况（包括性取向）··· ··· 如果医生的行为不道德或提供不适当的治疗，公众可以向新加坡医学委员会（SMC）提出正式投诉。”<ref>{{Cite web|title=Government's Stance on Changing One's Sexual Orientation through "Conversion Therapy"|url=https://www.moh.gov.sg/news-highlights/details/government's-stance-on-changing-one's-sexual-orientation-through-conversion-therapy|access-date=2021-06-23|date=2020-05-04|website=新加坡卫生部|archive-date=2021-06-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210628151815/https://www.moh.gov.sg/news-highlights/details/government%27s-stance-on-changing-one%27s-sexual-orientation-through-conversion-therapy}}</ref>尽管如此，他在另一份声明中补充说，卫生部在过去三年中没有收到任何来自 LGBTQ 患者的此类投诉。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Complaints about Psychiatrists, Psychologists and Counsellors from LGBTQ Clients|url=https://www.moh.gov.sg/news-highlights/details/complaints-about-psychiatrists-psychologists-and-counsellors-from-lgbtq-clients|access-date=2021-06-23|date=2020-05-05|website=新加坡卫生部|archive-date=2022-05-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220531064956/https://www.moh.gov.sg/news-highlights/details/complaints-about-psychiatrists-psychologists-and-counsellors-from-lgbtq-clients}}</ref>

==现状==
尽管新加坡存在反同性性行为的法律，但新加坡政府代表此前曾在联合国反歧视委员会对LGBT公民所面临的情况给予了积极的评价，称“同性恋者可以自由地过自己的生活并从事社交活动。同性恋群体已经举行了公开讨论并发布网站，新加坡有同性恋主题的电影和戏剧以及同性恋酒吧和俱乐部。”<ref name="economist" />

=== 传媒限制 ===
限制新加坡媒体发展局禁止在电视和广播中“宣传或美化同性恋生活方式”。这意味着媒体不允许出版、播放针对LGBT社区的广告。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/lgbt-singapore_us_561633d5e4b0e66ad4c67fe7|title=How One Of The World's Richest Countries Is Limiting Basic Human Rights|first=Dominique|last=Mosbergen|date=13 October 2015|via=Huff Post|newspaper=Huffington Post|access-date=15 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180811063256/https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/lgbt-singapore_us_561633d5e4b0e66ad4c67fe7|archive-date=11 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>

2019年7月，新加坡说唱歌手Joshua Su（也叫“The G3sha”） ，在一首名为“I'm OK”的新歌中以同性恋身份出柜，这首歌曲突出了他的童年、他所面临的恐同情绪以及他对自己的性取向的接受。<ref>{{cite web|title=Singapore rapper comes out as gay in song, recalls childhood when he 'didn't have anyone to turn to'|url=https://www.scmp.com/lifestyle/entertainment/article/3017819/singapore-rapper-comes-out-gay-new-song-tells-his-struggle|access-date=2019-07-18|date=2019-07-10|last=Frois|first=Andre|work=South China Morning Post|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190718022514/https://www.scmp.com/lifestyle/entertainment/article/3017819/singapore-rapper-comes-out-gay-new-song-tells-his-struggle|archive-date=2019-07-18|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title="I'm OK", a song about a gay guy's journey by Singaporean Joshua Su makes its debut|url=http://theindependent.sg/im-ok-a-song-about-a-gay-guys-journey-by-singaporean-joshua-su-makes-its-debut/|access-date=2019-07-18|date=2019-07-04|last=Koh|first=Lydia|work=The Independent News|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190704034726/http://www.theindependent.sg/im-ok-a-song-about-a-gay-guys-journey-by-singaporean-joshua-su-makes-its-debut/|archive-date=2019-07-04|url-status=live}}</ref>几天后，他在接受审查并要求不要对他的性取向发表“敏感”评论后退出 TEDx 电台演讲以示抗议。有报道称，在2018年，有另一位新加坡宣扬同性恋权利的社运人士被禁止在 TEDx 电台演讲中发言。<ref>{{cite web|title=Gay DJ pulls out of Singapore TEDx talk over censorship|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-singapore-lgbt-rights/gay-dj-pulls-out-of-singapore-tedx-talk-over-censorship-idUSKCN1TZ1ZB|access-date=2019-07-18|date=2019-07-04|work=Reuters|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190718022514/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-singapore-lgbt-rights/gay-dj-pulls-out-of-singapore-tedx-talk-over-censorship-idUSKCN1TZ1ZB|archive-date=2019-07-18|location=吉隆坡|url-status=live}}</ref>

=== 民意调查 ===
[[南洋理工大学|南洋理工大学]]2005年的一项民意调查发现，69%的新加坡人对同性恋持消极态度，而23%的人持积极态度。2010年，这两个数据分别变为64.5%和25%。<ref name="today">{{cite news|url=https://www.todayonline.com/big-read/big-read-house-still-divided-over-377a-time-seek-common-ground|title=The Big Read: With a house still divided over 377A, time to seek common ground|work=Today|location=新加坡|first=Faris|last=Mokhtar|date=2018-09-15|access-date=2018-09-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180930232045/https://www.todayonline.com/big-read/big-read-house-still-divided-over-377a-time-seek-common-ground|archive-date=2018-09-30|url-status=live}}</ref>

根据新加坡政策研究所2013年进行的民意调查，78%的新加坡人对同性婚姻持反对态度。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://mobile.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN0EY0SB20140623|title=Wear white to protest pink gay rally, religious groups say|date=2014-06-23|agency=路透社 Reuters|access-date=2015-11-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151121043716/http://mobile.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN0EY0SB20140623|archive-date=2015-11-21|url-status=live}}</ref>

2018年的一项民意调查指出，55%的新加坡人认为男同性恋者不应享有隐私权。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/55-of-spore-residents-still-support-gay-law-poll|title=55 per cent of Singapore residents still support gay law: Poll|first=Gilaine|last=Ng|date=2018-09-11|newspaper=The Straits Times|location=新加坡|access-date=2018-09-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180930231651/https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/55-of-spore-residents-still-support-gay-law-poll|archive-date=2018-09-30|url-status=live}}</ref>另一方面，与五年前相比，三分之一的新加坡人表示自己更能接受同性关系和其人权。

新加坡政策研究所在2018年8月至2019年1月期间进行的一项调查显示，新加坡社会在很大程度上仍然是保守的，但在认同 LGBT 权益方面变得更加自由。调查显示，超过20%的人表示同性成年人之间的性关系完全没有错或大部分时间没有错，比2013年上升了约10%。大约27%的人对同性婚姻持有同样的看法（高于2013年的15%），30%的人则对同性伴侣收养孩子持同样的看法（高于2013年的24%）。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/politics/greater-public-acceptance-of-gay-sex-and-marriage-survey|title=Greater public acceptance of gay sex and marriage: Survey|work=The Straits Times|location=新加坡|date=2019-05-03|access-date=2019-06-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190605181541/https://www.straitstimes.com/politics/greater-public-acceptance-of-gay-sex-and-marriage-survey|archive-date=2019-06-05|url-status=live|publisher=海峽時報}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/politics/singapore-society-still-largely-conservative-but-becoming-more-liberal-on-gay-rights-ips|title=Singapore society still largely conservative but becoming more liberal on gay rights: IPS survey|work=The Straits Times|location=新加坡|date=2019-05-02|last=Yuen-C|first=Tham|access-date=2019-06-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190605181337/https://www.straitstimes.com/politics/singapore-society-still-largely-conservative-but-becoming-more-liberal-on-gay-rights-ips|archive-date=2019-06-05|url-status=live|publisher=海峽時報}}</ref>

新加坡政策研究所在2019年进行的一项民意调查发现，新加坡反对同性婚姻的人数已从2013年的74%下降至60%。民意调查还发现，年龄在18至25岁之间的新加坡人中，有近60%的人认为相同性婚姻没有错。<ref>{{cite news|title=Support for gay rights seen growing in Singapore|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-singapore-lgbt-poll/support-for-gay-rights-seen-growing-in-singapore-idUSKCN1S81H9|agency=Reuters|author=Beh Lih Yi|date=2019-05-02|access-date=2019-05-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190502203603/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-singapore-lgbt-poll/support-for-gay-rights-seen-growing-in-singapore-idUSKCN1S81H9|archive-date=2019-05-02|url-status=live}}</ref>

2021年10月，一项由《今日报》（{{Lang-en|Today}}）举行的针对1066名介于18至35岁的年轻人的调查指出，80%的受访者愿意与 LGBTQ 人士一起工作、75%愿意与他们建立亲密的友谊、58%则表示愿意接受 LGBTQ 家庭成员；突显青年人对 LGBTQ 人群的总体接受度较高。<ref>{{Cite web|title=TODAY Youth Survey: High overall acceptance of LGBTQ people among youth, but family members having same-sex relationships harder to accept|url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/today-youth-survey-high-overall-acceptance-lgbtq-people-among-youth-family-members-harder-to-accept|access-date=2022-03-06|author=NABILAH AWANG|date=2021-11-11|publisher=今日报 Today|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120110921/https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/today-youth-survey-high-overall-acceptance-lgbtq-people-among-youth-family-members-harder-to-accept|archive-date=2022-01-20}}</ref>

=== 人口统计 ===
2019年5月，新加坡国立大学的一项调查估计，新加坡有21万名男性曾有过同性性行为。该调查所得数据是之前估计的90,000名男性的两倍多，报告里也提及他们可能面临艾滋病毒集中流行的风险。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.gaystarnews.com/article/study-finds-there-are-210000-men-who-have-sex-with-men-in-singapore/|title=Study finds there are 210,000 men who have sex with men in Singapore|work=Gay Star News|location=[[伦敦|伦敦]]|date=2019-06-05|last=Glauert|first=Rik|access-date=2019-06-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190605181835/https://www.gaystarnews.com/article/study-finds-there-are-210000-men-who-have-sex-with-men-in-singapore/|archive-date=2019-06-05|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/study-estimates-210000-men-who-have-sex-men-spore-risk-hiv|title=Study estimates 210,000 men who have sex with men in S'pore, at risk of HIV|work=今日报 Today|location=新加坡|date=2019-06-04|access-date=2019-06-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190605174256/https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/study-estimates-210000-men-who-have-sex-men-spore-risk-hiv|archive-date=2019-06-05|url-status=live}}</ref>

